This is not territory on which I feel very familiar, but
* the user input, the comment, is already laundered via the GitHub variables (this is something that actionlint warns against and it is taken care in this case);
* `printf '%s\n' "$var"` seems to be "the standard way" of avoiding the string to perform its own formatting and creating possible issues;
* `sed` receives the string through the pipe and I *think* that this is safe; in particular, nothing expands inside the `sed` call, since the script is surrounded by single quotes (`'`) and not by double quotes (`"`).

Does this sound convincing?  By the way, I think that these security concerns probably already applied to the older script: this is not to say that it is already safe, but that, if there are any concerns, we should also clean up the rest!  :smile:
